text: Sofia Polcanova (born 3 September 1994 in Chișinău) is an Moldovan-Austrian table tennis player. She competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in the women's singles event, in which she was eliminated in the second round by Jian Fang Lay, and as part of the Austrian team in the women's team event. ==References== Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Austrian female table tennis players Category:Moldovan table tennis players Category:Female table tennis players Category:Olympic table tennis players of Austria Category:Table tennis players at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Chișinău Category:Moldovan emigrants to Austria Category:Austrian expatriate sportspeople Category:Moldovan expatriate sportspeople Category:Naturalised citizens of Austria Category:Table tennis players at the 2015 European Games Category:Table tennis players at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games competitors for Austria Category:Kinoshita Abyell Kanagawa players Category:Naturalised table tennis players Category:Expatriate table tennis people in Japan
